<code>IDBIndex</code> interface of the <a href="/en/IndexedDB" title="en/IndexedDB">IndexedDB API</a> provides asynchronous access to an <a href="/en/IndexedDB/Basic_Concepts_Behind_IndexedDB#gloss_index" title="en/IndexedDB/Basic_Concepts_Behind_IndexedDB#gloss_index">index</a> in a database. An index is a kind of object store for looking up records in another object store, called the referenced object store. You use this interface to retrieve data.